title: For Sale:  Iraqi Contractor AK-47 WASR 10/63
postcontent:
Here is a now hard-to-find Iraqi Contractor 10/63 Romanian semi-automatic AKM.
 
These WASR 10-63s were made in Romania using cold hammer forged barrels. They were imported to the US by Century International Arms (CAI) either as kits or as sporting arms.
This rifle was amongst those subsequently sold en masse to SOC, a US contractor, who provided security services in Iraq for US installations.
SOC hired primarily Ugandans, many of whom, had been in the Ugandan Army and who were familiar with the AK-47. Take a look at the photos here. Due to Iraqi law, these paramilitary forces were not authorized fully automatic weapons. As a result, they were issued these WASRs, some Romanian semi auto RPKs; plus some AR-15 semiautomatics. These Ugandan men guarded the outer perimeter and other inner perimeter areas thereby freeing US personal to take the fight outside the wire. Though not a glamorous duty some contract guards came under fire and some were killed by suicide bombers.This rifle was hardly fired and nothing was wiped off just as it came back from Century including the dust from the desert. Origianl Romy G with Orignial military barrel with markings!
